            <fr:title text="chain reduction generated by a discrete vector field">chain reduction generated by a discrete vector field</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Intuition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  The <fr:link href="/forest/hmlg-001R/" title="chain reduction generated by a discrete vector field" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/hmlg-001R/" display-uri="hmlg-001R" type="local">chain reduction generated by a discrete vector field</fr:link> reduces an ACC <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(C_k, d)]]></fr:tex> to a smaller one, which can be explicitly described. Its cells are the critical cells in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_k]]></fr:tex>. For the faces of a cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>, we start with the faces <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(\sigma )]]></fr:tex> in the original ACC. Then we move every non-critical cell down along the <fr:link href="/forest/hmlg-001Q/" title="discrete field line" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/hmlg-001Q/" display-uri="hmlg-001Q" type="local">discrete field lines</fr:link>, up to some sign flips, until we get to a critical cell.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  Note that the field lines alternate between <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>- and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(n+1)]]></fr:tex>-dimensional cells, and we count the movement <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> – <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(n+1)]]></fr:tex> – <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> as a single step. Also, <fr:link href="/forest/hmlg-001S/" title="discrete field lines can branch and merge" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/hmlg-001S/" display-uri="hmlg-001S" type="local">discrete field lines can branch and merge</fr:link>, and the cells need to duplicate and move down every branch.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
