            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>4</fr:month>
              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/hmlg-001Q/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>hmlg-001Q</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/forest/hmlg-001Q/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="discrete field line">discrete field line</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Given a <fr:link href="/forest/hmlg-001N/" title="discrete vector field" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/hmlg-001N/" display-uri="hmlg-001N" type="local">discrete vector field</fr:link>, the discrete version of <html:strong>field lines</html:strong> is defined as a sequence of cells alternating between degree <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(p-1)]]></fr:tex> starting and ending with lower-degree cells, with a few requirements.
</html:p>
            <html:ul><html:li>When the degree increases, the two cells must occur as a vector in the DVF.</html:li>
  <html:li>When the degree decreases, the degree <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(p-1)]]></fr:tex> cell must be a (possible non-<fr:link href="/forest/hmlg-001O/" title="regular face in an algebraic cellular complex" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/hmlg-001O/" display-uri="hmlg-001O" type="local">regular</fr:link>) face of the degree <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> cell.</html:li>
  <html:li>Two degree <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(p-1)]]></fr:tex> cells separated by a degree <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> cell must not be the same.</html:li></html:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
